-- Poland's insurer PZU buys Baltic rivals for $365 million
-- 
-- Thu Apr 17, 2014 02:23AM EDT
-- None



WARSAW, April 17 (Reuters) - Central and eastern Europe's largest insurer PZU <PZU.WA> has bought three Baltic rivals for a total of $356 million, pending adjustments, PZU said in a statement on Thursday.

PZU said it bought Lithuania's Lietuvos Draudimas and Latvian AAS Balta from the British group RSA <RSA.L>. PZU added that it purchased the Estonian unit of Denmark's Codan Forsikring.